'''Infini''' is a [[computer reservations system]] based in Japan which provides its services in the Japanese market. It was created in 1990 by [[All Nippon Airways]] and [[Abacus (GDS)]] who currently own 100% of Infini.<ref>{{cite web|title=Corporate Profile |url=http://www.infini-trvl.co.jp/english/corporate/profile.html |publisher=www.infini-trvl.co.jp |accessdate=4 February 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050306090217/http://www.infini-trvl.co.jp/english/corporate/profile.html |archivedate=March 6, 2005 }}</ref> It utilises technology from [[Sabre Holdings]] to provide booking and ticketing capabilities to travel agencies in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.odysseymediagroup.com/apn/Editorial-Travel-Management.asp?ReportID=16449 |title=Travel Management - INFINI Successfully Migrates Its Core CRS To Sabre Platform System |publisher=Odysseymediagroup.com |date=2000-11-13 |accessdate=2013-10-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sabre History |url=http://en.me.sabretravelnetwork.com/home/about/history/ |publisher=en.me.sabretravelnetwork.com |accessdate=4 February 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120426043829/http://en.me.sabretravelnetwork.com/home/about/history/ |archivedate=April 26, 2012 }}</ref>

