'''Waldemar Kita''' (born 1953 in [[Szczecin]], [[Poland]]) is a [[Poland|Polish]] businessman residing in [[France]].<ref name="kita1">[http://www.boursier.com/vals/all/football-waldemar-kita-s-offre-le-fc-nantes-feed-27343.htm Waldemar Kita s'offre le FC Nantes], Boursier.com et Reuters, published 28 July 2007, retrieved on 10 June 2009.</ref>

==Optics==

Kita made his fortune by establishing Cornéal in 1986. The company grew to become the foremost French, and fourth largest European firm designing and manufacturing [[intraocular lens]]es for cataract surgery and in the treatment of glaucoma. In December 2006, Kita sold Cornéal to [[Allergan]] for 180 million [[euro]]s.<ref name="kita2">[http://www.bienvoir.com/news/index.php?val=605_allergan+acquiert+francais+corneal+pour+se+renforcer+sur+marche+antirides Allergan, acquiert le français Corneal], Bienvoir.com, published 9 November 2006, retrieved on 10 June 2009.</ref>

==Football==

He is now chairman of [[FC Nantes]]. "Reports claim Kita paid 10 million euros for the club, which has won eight French championships and is considered one of France's most important."<ref name=extra>[http://www.extra-football.com/articles/waldemar-kita-bought-fc-nantes-10-million-serge-dassault.html "Polish businessman Waldemar Kita buys Nantes" by ''Extra Football'', 29 July 2007], retrieved on 15 September 2008.</ref>

"Kita is a familiar face in the world of football as the contact lens tycoon bought Swiss club Lausanne and led them between 1998 and 2001."<ref name=extra/>

