a (second generation)|Subaru Impreza]] * 2001 [[Holden Barina#XC|Holden XC Barina]] * 2002 [[Ford BA Falcon]] * 2003 [[Mazda RX-8]]{{efn|First [[rotary engine]]d winner}} * 2004 [[Ford Territory (Australia)|Ford SX Territory]]{{efn|First [[sport utility vehicle]] (SUV) winner}} * 2005 [[Mazda MX-5#NC|Mazda MX-5 (NC)]] * 2006 [[Holden VE Calais]]{{efn|name=last Australian-made|Last Australian-made vehicle to win COTY}} * 2007 [[Mercedes-Benz C-Class (W204)]] * 2008 [[Honda Accord (Japan and Europe eighth generation)|Honda Accord Euro]] * 2009 [[Volkswagen Golf Mk6]] * 2010 [[Volkswagen Polo Mk5]] * 2011 [[Honda CR-Z]]{{efn|First [[hybrid vehicle]] winner}} * 2012 [[Toyota 86|Toyota 86 and Subaru BRZ]]{{efn|name=badge engineered}} * 2013 [[Volkswagen Golf Mk7]] * 2014 [[BMW i3]] * 2015 – temporal basis for award changed * 2016 [[Mazda MX-5#ND|Mazda MX-5 (ND)]] * 2017 [[Mazda CX-9#Second Generation (2016-present)|Mazda CX-9]] * 2018 [[Volvo XC60]] }}
